11/10/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- War crimes suspect Predrag Kujundzic was arrested in the town of Doboj, Republika Srpska (RS), prosecutors announced on Wednesday (October 10th). 
Kujundzic, 46, is suspected of committing war crimes against Bosniak and Croats civilians in 1992 and 1993, when he was commander of the Predini vukovi (Predo's Wolves) paramilitary formation that was attached to the RS Army in the Doboj area. 
For the past few years he has been on the black list of suspected supporters of war crimes fugitive Radovan Karadzic. 
((Nezavisne Novine - 11/10/07; B92, Beta, BIRN, DPA - 10/10/07)
